Make nestia.config.ts file and run npx nestia swagger command.At first, create nestia.config.ts file through npx nestia init command. It would be placed on the top level directory of your NestJS backend project. For reference, tsconfig.json file also must be placed in the top level directory, too. After creation, configure the nestia.config.ts file referencing above example code and type definition.At least, you've to configure those two properties:
input: Accessor of controller classes
swagger.output: Path of swagger.json file
When you've completed above configuration, just run npx nestia swagger command. Then, swagger.json file would be newly generated, and placed into the $config.swagger.output directory following your nestia.config.ts configuration.

